  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Toast whole spices in ghee, then sauté onion, garlic and ginger. Toast ground spices 30 seconds, add tomato, salt, stock and lamb. Simmer gently covered 1 hr 45 min until lamb fork-tender, simmer with lid off 15 min to reduce. Stir in Finishes, serve!"
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Toast whole spices - Melt ghee over medium heat in large heavy based pot. Add cinnamon, cardamom and cloves and cook for one minute."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Sauté - Add onion and cook for 7 minutes, stirring frequently, until pieces are golden and starting the brown on the edges. Add the garlic and ginger, cook for another minute."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Toast spices - Stir in the Spices, cook for 30 seconds."
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "instruction": "Sauce and lamb - Mix in the tomato puree and salt, then add stock and mix. Add lamb, stir, bring to simmer."
    },
    {
      "order": 6,
      "instruction": "Simmer 1 h 45 min - Place lid on and adjust heat to low or medium low so it&#39;s simmering gently. Cook 1 hour 45 minutes, giving it an occasional stir, until lamb is quite tender - use 2 forks to check, it should pry apart pretty easily."
    },
    {
      "order": 7,
      "instruction": "Reduce - Remove lid, and continue cooking for another 15 minutes (to reduce sauce slightly) - lamb should be very tender by this stage."
    },
    {
      "order": 8,
      "instruction": "Finish - Stir in the Yogurt, the Extra garam marsala and fennel. Cook for another few minutes."
    },
    {
      "order": 9,
      "instruction": "Serve with basmati rice, sprinkled with fresh coriander leaves and other garnishes if desired. More sides (pictured): Cucumber salad (Note 7) and Easy naan - No Yeast Flatbread"
    }
  ]
}